These are the three aspects of organizational culture: Innovation and calculated risk-taking: This metric measures the degree to which an organization supports and rewards innovation and calculated risk-taking. Google, which is renowned for its 20% time policy in which workers are granted 20% of their work time to pursue projects of their own interest, is an example of this dimension. This dimension describes the amount of accuracy and thoroughness an organization expects from its work procedures. Tesla exemplifies this characteristic since it stresses attention to detail in its production process to assure the quality of its goods. This dimension describes the degree to which a corporation focuses on accomplishing specified goals and objectives. This dimension is shown by Amazon, which is renowned for its dedication to reaching performance goals and continually enhancing its operations. 